===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|writen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|wrītan|t=to incise, engrave, write, draw, bestow by writing}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*wrītan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wrītaną|t=to carve, write}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*wrey-|t=to rip, tear}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|write|t=to wear by rubbing, rip, tear}}, {{cog|nl|wrijten|t=to argue, quarrel}}, {{cog|gml|wrîten|t=to scratch, draw, write}} (> {{cog|nds|wrieten}}, {{m|nds|rieten|t=to tear, split}}), {{cog|de|reißen|t=to tear, rip}}, {{cog|no|rita|t=to rough-sketch, carve, write}}, {{cog|sv|rita|t=to draw, design, delineate, model}}, {{cog|is|rita|t=to cut, scratch, write}}, {{cog|de|ritzen|t=to carve, scratch}}, {{cog|sla-pro|*ryti|t=to carve, engrave, dig}}, {{cog|pl|ryć|t=to engrave, dig}}, {{cog|cs|rýt|t=to engrave, dig}}. See also [[rit]] and [[rat]].

